message.content:
As a 40-year-old male Professor in psychology, I would respond to the survey questions as follows:

Q1: 1: I did not find myself getting upset by trivial things as I am generally able to maintain perspective and composure.
Q2: 1: I did not experience any dryness in my mouth as I have been adequately hydrated and managing stress effectively.
Q3: 1: I have been able to experience positive feelings, especially seeing my students excel in their understanding of psychology.
Q4: 1: I did not experience any breathing difficulties as I have been practicing mindfulness and relaxation techniques regularly.
Q5: 1: I have been able to stay motivated and productive in my work and personal life.
Q6: 1: I have been able to remain calm and rational in various situations without over-reacting.
Q7: 1: I did not feel any shakiness as I have been maintaining a healthy lifestyle and managing stress effectively.
Q8: 1: I have been able to relax and unwind after work, engaging in activities that bring me joy and relaxation.
Q9: 1: I did not find myself in highly anxious situations that made me relieved when they ended.
Q10: 1: I have many things to look forward to, both professionally and personally.
Q11: 1: I did not get upset easily as I have a good sense of emotional regulation.
Q12: 1: I have been managing my energy levels well and not feeling excessively nervous.
Q13: 1: I have not felt sad or depressed, finding fulfillment in my work and personal life.
Q14: 1: I have been patient and understanding, not getting agitated by delays or inconveniences.
Q15: 1: I did not experience any feelings of faintness as I have been prioritizing my physical health.
Q16: 1: I have maintained interest in various activities and continue to find enjoyment in them.
Q17: 1: I have a strong sense of self-worth and do not feel unworthy as a person.
Q18: 1: I have not been touchy or easily irritated in my interactions with others.
Q19: 1: I did not experience noticeable perspiration in the absence of physical exertion.
Q20: 1: I have not felt scared without reason and have been able to manage any anxiety effectively.
Q21: 1: I find life worthwhile and full of meaning, with various opportunities for growth and fulfillment.
Q22: 1: I have been able to wind down and relax after a busy day, not finding it difficult to do so.
Q23: 1: I did not experience difficulty in swallowing, indicating a lack of severe stress or anxiety.
Q24: 1: I have been able to derive enjoyment from the activities I engage in, feeling satisfied with my choices.
Q25: 1: I did not notice any irregularities in my heart rate or palpitations in the absence of physical exertion.
Q26: 1: I have not felt down-hearted or blue, maintaining a positive outlook on life.
Q27: 1: I have not been irritable and have maintained a calm and composed demeanor.
Q28: 1: I have not felt close to panic in any situations, being able to manage stress effectively.
Q29: 1: I have been able to calm down quickly after being upset, not lingering on negative emotions.
Q30: 1: I have not feared being thrown by trivial tasks, approaching challenges with confidence and competence.
Q31: 1: I have maintained enthusiasm for my work and interests, finding joy in learning and teaching.
Q32: 1: I have been able to tolerate interruptions and adapt to changing circumstances without difficulty.
Q33: 1: I have not been in a state of nervous tension, maintaining a sense of calm and collectedness.
Q34: 1: I have a strong sense of self-worth and do not feel pretty worthless as a person.
Q35: 1: I have been patient with interruptions and have not been intolerant of disruptions in my work.
Q36: 1: I have not felt terrified, maintaining a sense of security and confidence in my life.
Q37: 1: I see a hopeful future ahead with various opportunities for growth and fulfillment.
Q38: 1: I find life meaningful and purposeful, with opportunities for personal and professional development.
Q39: 1: I have not been agitated and have maintained a sense of calm and composure.
Q40: 1: I have not worried about panicking in situations and making a fool of myself, trusting in my abilities and competence.
Q41: 1: I did not experience trembling in my hands, indicating a lack of severe stress or anxiety.
Q42: 1: I have been able to work up initiative and motivation to accomplish tasks effectively and efficiently.
